Name: Intermediate Climbing
Description: Enhance and further develop climbing skills and knowledge. Climbers will learn terminology, follow graded routes, and climbing methods such as matching, smearing, flagging, and more. Must pass a beginner class and receive instructor approval before registering.

Name: Taekwondo
Description: A Korean art using hands and feet as a means of practical self-defense is recognized as the national sport of Korea as well as an Olympic sport.

Name: Climb Time
Description: A climbing class open to all skill levels in which the goal is to have fun in games and activities while improving upon your current skills.

Name: Adult Open Gym
Description: Drop-in to the gym for adult sports like basketball, pickleball, and volleyball.

Name: Certified Climb
Description: Members who are YMCA Belay Certified are offered time to use the wall at their leisure. Certified members may bring a non-certified member while in this program. Ages 5-7 must have direct visual supervision by a guardian. Members who have previous belaying experience can be tested during this time with a staff member in order to gain Belay Certification.

Name: Wheelchair Sports
Description: Wheelchair Sports offers traditional sports adapted to participants' unique needs. Children also enjoy getting out of their chairs to enjoy activities like being spun on the giant rainbow parachute, or being pulled around on the four-wheeled scooter.

Name: YMCA Diabetes Prevention Program
Description: The program provides a supportive environment where participants work together in a small group to learn about healthier eating and increasing their physical activity in order to reduce their risk for developing diabetes. The program, which is led by a trained lifestyle coach in a classroom setting, is delivered over a 12-month period, beginning with 16 weekly sessions followed by monthly maintenance. The YMCA Diabetes Prevention Program is part of the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention-led National Diabetes Prevention Program and is nationally supported by the Diabetes Prevention and Control Alliance.

Name: Youth Sports Mix
Description: Experience a variety of traditional sports and playground style games through warm ups, skills, drills, and scrimmages.

Name: YMCA Weight Loss Program
Description: In a classroom setting, a trained lifestyle coach facilitates a small group of up to 16 participants in learning about healthier eating, physical activity and other behavior changes over the course of 12 one-hour sessions. The program introduces participants to behaviors that have been shown to lead to sustained weight loss, and help participants develop those behaviors in ways that fit into their personal lifestyle. With the tools provided in the program, along with the knowledge and support of the group, participants develop their own nutrition and exercise plans that work for them.

Name: Toddler Sports Mix
Description: This parent/child offering encourages an educational and fun sports experience by providing a baseline introduction to a variety of sports, utilizing age-appropriate stations to play various sports.

Name: ACT! Actively Changing Together
Description: The ACT! Actively Changing Together program is for children ages 8-14 and their parents. This 12 week program promotes healthy nutrition, activity and lifestyles developed in partnership with providers and professionals. The ACT! Program appeals to children and parents alike by providing engaging, fun, and unique activities. By actively changing together, parents and kids can learn how to form healthy lifestyle habits as a family. Specially trained Y staff offer guidance and encouragement for eating well, playing often, and preventing health conditions associated with being overweight. Referrals are welcome year-round.

Name: Martial Arts Beginning
Description: Classes begin and end with warm-ups, stretching, and meditation. Participants learn beginning skills for striking, blocking, and movement in addition to proper falling techniques and practical self-defense techniques.

Name: Adult Pickleball
Description: Learn to serve, lob, overhead, and volley.

Name: Journey to Healthy Living
Description: Managing your weight is complicated, including our relationship with food and our body, feelings of self-worth, stress, and emotional health. Successfully changing your lifestyle requires a comprehensive approach. Journey to Healthy Living is an eight-week small group which meets for two hours once a week. This program includes an introduction to exercise, book discussion, and information on healthy eating. Experience a supportive community as you create your own holistic weight management plan while engaging your spirit, mind, and body.

Name: Adult Volleyball
Description: Learn serving, setting, passing, hitting, and blocking, as well as concepts of offense and defense.

Name: Women's Wellness Weekend
Description: A weekend of instructional classes including yoga, arts and crafts, kayaking, archery, and climbing designed to help women grow in mind and body.

Name: Gymnastics Boys Beginner
Description: Classes provide instruction on men's competitive events and trampoline.  Participants develop body awareness and improve strength and flexibility.

Name: Women on Weights
Description: Experience a variety of workouts using different weight room equipment. Learn about proper weight room form and technique and stay motivated by pre and post program strength tests.

Name: Gymnastics Boys Intermediate
Description: Testing out of the Beginner level required. This class builds on the basic skills achieved in Beginner Gymnastics, and further develops coordination, strength, and flexibility. Prepares gymnasts for the Advanced Gymnastics class.

Name: Gymnastics Girls Beginner 1
Description: Classes provide instruction on gymnastics equipment and skills. Participants develop body awareness and improve strength and flexibility and learn the fundamentals of gymnastics skills and terminology.

Name: Low Impact Classic
Description: Description Needed

Name: Gymnastics Girls Beginner 2
Description: Testing out of beginning level or prior gymnastics training of beginning gymnastics classes required. This class builds on skills learned in Beginning 1 and introduces gymnasts to additional beginning skills and terminology.

Name: Walking Wellness
Description: This class is great for beginning fitness or for those who just enjoy walking. Each session includes a warm up, walk, and cool down section.

Name: Gymnastics Girls Intermediate
Description: Testing out of the Beginner level required. This class builds on the basic skills achieved in Beginner Gymnastics, and further develops coordination, strength, and flexibility. Prepares gymnasts for the Advanced Gymnastics class.

Name: Homeschool PE
Description: Age appropriate skill development drills teach general fitness, sports, balance, teamwork, and more. Open to all homeschooled children during the school year and included in your YMCA membership.

Name: Gymnastics Girls Advanced 1
Description: Testing out of the Intermediate level required. This class builds on the skills achieved in Intermediate Gymnastics, and challenges gymnasts to a new level of coordination, strength, and flexibility.

Name: Preschool Fitness Fun
Description: A complete fitness class for children that introduces them to full body strength and conditioning training. Training includes pushups, squats, agility ladder, jump rope, and sports games.

Name: Pre-Teen Fitness
Description: Pre-teens of all fitness levels get active and make friends through fun and exercise. With a focus on fitness, activities improve cardio, resistance training, and agility through structured exercise and games

Name: School Age 1/2 Acclimation/Movement
Description: Focuses on exploring body positions, blowing bubbles, and fundamental safety and aquatic skills

Name: School Age 4 - Stoke Introduction
Description: Introduces breaststroke and butterfly and reinforces water safety through treading water and sidestroke

Name: Gymnastics Boys Advanced
Description: Testing out of the Intermediate level required. This class builds on the skills achieved in Intermediate Gymnastics, and challenges gymnasts to a new level of coordination, strength, and flexibility.

Name: 6 | Stroke Mechanics
Description: Refines stroke technique on all major competitive strokes and encourages swimming as part of a healthy lifestyle

Name: Youth Private Swim Lessons
Description: Private and semi-private swimming lessons are available for an additional fee.

Name: Lifeguard Certification
Description: Learn to lifeguard in a variety of settings including pool, lake, river, surf, and water park. Earn certifications: YMCA Lifeguard, First Aid, CPR for the Professional Rescuer, AED, and Oxygen Administration.

Name: Safety Around Water
Description: Participants will learn how to front and back float, jump in and return to the edge of the pool, and to kick on their front and back for ten feet. Participants will also learn how to use a personal floatation device.

Name: Basic Life Support CPR/AED/Oxygen/Basic First Aid Certification
Description: Join our ASHI certified instructors to learn basic lifesaving techniques. After completing a five-and-a-half hour online learning course and attending an in-person class, you will be certified in Basic Life Support (CPR/AED) Oxygen, and Basic First Aid by the American Health and Safety Institute.

Name: Swim Team
Description: Engage in competitive swimming with a goal-focused emphasis. Swim team participation promotes sportsmanship, self-esteem, self-discipline, self-improvement, and social interaction. Participants must be at least at the Stroke Mechanics swimming level.

Name: Parent/Child Music
Description: Music concepts are introduced through the teaching of imagination, self-expression and group interaction. Parental participation is required in this class.

Name: Musical Theater
Description: Move beyond the basics of musical theater as a complete performance is created.

Name: Piano
Description: Semi-private and private lessons are customizable for a specific interests and diverse ability levels. Pianists will increase their skill, knowledge, and music appreciation.

Name: Parent/Child Creative Movement
Description: Basic ballet movements and music concepts are introduced through the teaching of imagination, self-expression and group interaction. Parental participation is required in this class.

Name: Guitar
Description: This small group class teaches students basic guitar techniques. Students will learn how to read music, understand guitar tablature, play simple chords, and collaborate with other musicians.  Students bring their own instrument to class.

Name: Pre-Pointe and Pointe
Description: Classes are offered to advanced students focusing on body alignment, strengthening exercises, and transition to pointe. These classes are for ages 13-adult and are by invitation only.

Name: Theater
Description: Introduction to the foundational elements of performance. Classes include elements of acting, stagecraft, and classical theater skills.

Name: Ballroom Dance
Description: Stay active and have fun learning the Waltz, Foxtrot, Tango, Swing, Cha Cha and more. No partner required.

Name: Vocal
Description: Customizable for specific interests and diverse ability levels, vocalists will increase their skill and knowledge.

Name: Line Dancing
Description: Come join the fun and dance to a variety of music and styles.

Name: Ukulele
Description: A small group class that teaches students the basics of Ukulele technique. Students will also learn the history of the Ukulele and learn simple cords

Name: Hula
Description: Learn the basics of hula and the Hawaiian culture.

Name: Y Bakers - Beginning
Description: Y Bakers Beginners is class is fun introductory baking class for youth ages 7-12. We focus on introducing measuring skills, reading a recipe, and learning about the components of our food.  This session we are learning about bread and its varieties. Some highlights include Pizza and Cornbread.

Name: Jazz Funk
Description: Jazz Funk is a high energy dance style that offers a fusion of Jazz and Hip-Hop. Students will have an in class performance at the end of the session.

Name: Parent/Child Art
Description: Creativity is explored as parents and preschoolers engage in hands-on projects using varying art mediums. These classes teach kids and their caregivers to use their imagination, promoting self-expression and group interaction.

Name: Y Bakers - Intermediate
Description: Y Bakers Intermediate class is a slightly more advanced class that allows our students to explore new techniques and skills. Students will often be able to make choices on what variation of a recipe to make. This session we are learning about bread and its varieties. Highlights include Cinnamon Rolls and German Pretzels.

Name: Animation
Description: Learn the basic principles and techniques of animation using various software programs including Dragon Frame.

Name: Parent/Child Tot Chef
Description: These classes teach kids and their caregivers the basics of food preparation in this fun and delightfully messy class!

Name: Mixed Media
Description: Build a new visual vocabulary by learning about how to transform materials in this mixed media art class. Students will explore the seven elements of art by using a range of common materials and incorporating several art mediums in each project.

Name: Culinary Kids
Description: Children gain exposure to cooking principles, tools, and kitchen safety in these stand-alone workshops.  provide a relaxed and fun environment and food tasting at the end of class.

Name: Ceramics
Description: Students will learn the basics of creating in three-dimensions with clay in this fun and popular class. Participants will explore simple construction techniques including coil and slab building and the use of modeling tools.

Name: Culinary Arts 1
Description: Children master basic culinary skills in this fun weekly class. A pre-requisite to Culinary Kids 2.

Name: Drawing
Description: Drawing Level 1 students learn basic drawing techniques and create pencil and charcoal drawings from photographs and live scenery.

Name: Drawing and Painting
Description: Create using pencils, colored pencils, and watercolor.

Name: Dance Teachers in Training
Description: The Dance Teachers in Training program pairs teens with YMCA senior dance instructor mentors to nurture leadership potential and develop the teaching skills needed to lead beginning-level dance classes. Participants engage in a one- to two-year development track, including hands-on classroom instruction, one-on-one mentoring, and a comprehensive credit-based tracking system. Upon graduation, teens are given volunteer teaching opportunities within Y dance programs.

Name: Fashion Design
Description: Create various costume pieces to allow two separate costumes at completion of class.

Name: Break Dancing
Description: An introductory level class geared towards those interested in learning the basic movements and historical underpinnings of B-boy and B-girl culture.

Name: Jewelry Making
Description: Make wearable art in this creative and fun class.

Name: Irish Dance
Description: This high paced class introduces dancers to basic Irish dance movements jumping, hopping, skipping and pointing, counting the beats and having fun. Dancers will explore soft shoe jig and reel.

Name: Painting: Beginner, Intermediate, Advanced
Description: Learn painting techniques and increase your creativity with the use of watercolor and acrylic paints.

Name: Intro to Ballet
Description: Children learn the basics of ballet technique. Classes are designed as an introduction only prior to participating in regular preschool and ballet classes

Name: Preschool Ballet
Description: Focus on exploration of music and movement in this ballet introduction. Preschoolers discover their creativity through fun exercises and group interaction.

Name: Sewing
Description: Learn how to use a sewing machine and basic vocabulary skills for sewing with a pattern.

Name: Culinary Arts 2
Description: Youth, teens, and adults explore in-depth culinary arts curriculum, each class focuses on three recipes.

Name: Dance Recitals
Description: Annual dance recitals are offered to all dance program participants. Formal and informal performances are held at the Y and local theaters. Each dancer is highlighted and given the chance to shine.

Name: Artist Workshops
Description: Join local artists and Y instructors for a series of two-hour workshops designed to explore various art forms and unleash creativity.

Name: Ballet - Beginner-Advanced
Description: Beginning students learn preparatory exercises, focusing on creativity and exploration of movement. More advanced students engage in placement, technique, and musicality through barre, center, and enchainment (combination) exercises.

Name: Contemporary
Description: Explore natural energy and emotions that create dances of fluid expression while learning contact-release, floor work, fall and recovery, and improvisation.

Name: Digital Drawing and Painting
Description: Explore a variety of digital software that will enhance creativity and imagination as the principles of art are introduced.

Name: Hip Hop
Description: Master your floor work and footwork in this high-energy class, with a focus on rhythms, musicality, and individual expression.

Name: Robotics
Description: Build a robot using Lego Mindstorm. Students learn the basic mechanics of a robot while challenging their imagination and creativity. Simple programming concepts are also covered in this popular and fun class.

Name: Hula
Description: Learn the basics of hula and the Hawaiian culture.

Name: Movie Making
Description: Students will learn the basics of using a camera to capture original footage utilizing stop-motion Lego Moviemaker. This project-based class includes an overview of tools and techniques for making great short videos and sharing them with friends and family on YouTube.

Name: Photography
Description: Students will learn the basics of using a digital camera to take photos, how to import images to a computer, simple editing, and printing. This project-based class includes an overview of tools and techniques for making great photos and turning them into digital art.

Name: Lyrical
Description: A fusion of ballet, jazz, and modern dance, usually containing an emotional journey, or story.

Name: Salsa
Description: Learn introductory skills and techniques in salsa dancing.

Name: Tap
Description: Learn the technique, terminology and rhythm of tap dancing.

Name: Kayak Trip
Description: Teens participate in camp's challenge/adventure course and self-rescue training before leaving on a four night adventure in the Puget Sound. This beginner trip requires strong cardio and advanced swimming ability.

Name: Wilderness Adventure
Description: The positive staff role models of the Wilderness Adventure trip help teens build self-esteem, disconnect from distractions, and make new friends during a three-day backpack trip and two-day kayak trip.

Name: Quest - Grades 10-11
Description: Quest is an extended wilderness leadership program. Staff with extensive wilderness experience and advanced medical training lead this ten day paddling and backpacking adventure in the Olympic National Park.

Name: Lead – Grades 11-12
Description: Teens receive training in program planning, child development, relationship building, and service learning during this two-week camp. Time is spent building a system of support and communication to assist younger campers.

Name: Line Dancing
Description: At day camp, children make friendships, gain self-confidence, and are encouraged to model the Y values of caring, honesty, respect, and responsibility.

Name: Mini Campers
Description: Preschool campers will participate in a variety of activities centered on weekly themes and YMCA values including: swimming, gymnastics, dance, group games, crafts, story time, snacks and much more.

Name: Full Day Camp
Description: Day Camp provides a safe place for campers to make friends, learn new skills, and stay active. Throughout the summer, campers participate in values-based programs including swimming, sports, arts and crafts, team building games, and more. Swim lessons available at Mel Korum Family YMCA, Morgan Family YMCA, and YMCA Camp Seymour.

Name: Jazz
Description: Jazz combines many styles and techniques from ethnic and contemporary dance to ballet. This engaging and upbeat class emphasizes syncopation, strength, body alignment, and expression.

Name: Partial Day Camp
Description: From swimming to sports, small group games to large group activities, kids learn and play through activities that teach teamwork, sportsmanship, and skill development.

Name: Pioneers | Grades 2-3
Description: An introduction to overnight camp. Low camper to staff ratio ensures each camper feels supported in their experience. Campers travel together and sample activities like archery, boating, and climbing wall.

Name: Trailblazers | Grades 3-5
Description: Trailblazers learn about independence and acceptance. Campers choose to specialize in sports, crafts, or marine science activities in addition to choice time option including boating, climbing, games, crafts, and archery.

Name: Explorers | Grades 5-7
Description: Explorers choose daily "camptivities" like kayaking, climbing, water sports, crafts, soccer, basketball, marine science, outdoor adventure and/or performing arts. These camptivities are progressive, skill-building classes that foster confidence building.

Name: Adventurers | Grades 7-8
Description: Adventurers learn to accept others and to work together through challenge adventures, wilderness camping in the Olympic National Park, and participating in camp activities.

Name: Voyagers | Grades 8-9
Description: Campers already comfortable in a camp setting enjoy an environment that builds positive peer relationships, as well as teach tolerance of others and their ideas. Specialize in activities like: kayaking, climbing, specialized crafts, sports, outdoor living skills, and performing arts.

Name: Trek | Grades 9-10
Description: Trek campers focus on becoming leaders among their peers through challenge and adventure programming, an extended wilderness experience in the Olympic National Park, volunteer experiences, and outdoor camping experiences.

Name: Quest | Grades 10-11

Throughout the summer, campers participate in values-based programs including swimming, sports, arts and crafts, team building games, leadership opportunities, and field trips. Swim lessons available at Mel Korum Family YMCA, Morgan Family YMCA, and YMCA Camp Seymour.

Name: Specialty Camp
Description: Choose from a variety of activities to keep your child engaged and active throughout the summer. Afternoon activities change each week and include sports, alternative sports, dance, arts, science, and technology.

Name: Challenge Course
Description: The Challenge Course provides a team-building opportunity for your group to play and learn together through physical and mental challenges.

Name: Retreats and Conferences
Description: YMCA Camp Seymour hosts a variety of YMCA and non-YMCA groups (from 30-200 people) throughout the year, providing accommodations, meals, meeting space, and activities.

Name: Outdoor Environmental Education
Description: The Outdoor and Environmental Education program guides students in exploring ecosystems, understanding natural resources, and outdoor and group building skills. Classes are designed to enhance Washington State Essential Learning Standards.

Successfully changing your lifestyle requires a comprehensive approach. Journey to Healthy Living is an eight-week small group which meets for two hours once a week. This program includes an introduction to exercise, book discussion, and information on healthy eating. Experience a supportive community as you create your own holistic weight management plan while engaging your spirit, mind, and body.

Name: Alpha
Description: Explore the meaning of life in a relaxed, friendly setting while sharing a meal, short talk and discussion. All questions and opinions are welcomed from those with or without faith. Topics may include: Is there a God? Why am I here? Where did I come from? Where am I going?

Name: Safe Sitters Babysitting Training
Description: Covers skills required for a safe babysitter; supervision and play with children of various ages, basic child care, basic first aid, safety precautions, accident prevention, and critical emergency action skills.

Name: Counselor in Training
Description: During this two week summer camp, participants learn the skills necessary to be an effective summer camp counselor. Councelors in training may be offered volunteer positions for the remaining weeks of summer.

Name: Youth and Government
Description: Over the course of a school year, this non-partisan program provides middle and high school students the opportunity to become civically engaged through experience running a model state legislature.

Name: Kids Night Out Teen Leaders
Description: Teens work with children and peers earning them credit that can be applied toward Teen Leadership Development program fees and special events.

Name: Brotherhood
Description: Brotherhood offers a small group setting for male teens in a supportive, relaxed environment.

Name: Art Parties
Description: At an Art Party, participants work on art pieces under the careful instruction of a professional artist and among friends. Have fun and leave with your very own masterpiece.

Name: Sisterhood
Description: Sisterhood offers a small group setting for female teens in a supportive, relaxed environment.

Name: Pool Parties
Description: Make a splash at your next event with a pool party at the Y! Children and adults swim under the supervision of our trained lifeguards.

Name: Leadership Development Program
Description: Teens learn valuable skills while working with kids and participating in service learning projects at camp and in their communities. Teens may earn credit to help them pay for YMCA programs.

Name: Rock Wall Parties
Description: Climb to new heights at your next party! The rock wall provides a fun physical and mental challenge for all ages and ability levels. Participants will learn safety and basic climbing skills.

Name: Pacific Region Conference
Description: An annual retreat for teens that seek to create a community based on honesty, respect, responsibility, and trust. It enables teens to set and meet personal goals and build self-esteem.

Name: Little Learners
Description: Children enjoy instruction in reading, writing, counting and simple math, science, music, art, and more. Ideal for children learning a topic for the first time or to enhance and reinforce existing skills.

Name: Youth Leadership Development Conference
Description: Participants have the opportunity to meet new friends and participate in small group activities and discussions while learning new perspectives about themselves and the world around them.

Name: Little Einsteins
Description: An educational enrichment program where children learn about the wonders of their environment through exploration and discussion.

Name: Summer of Service
Description: Summer of Service is an annual teen service trip to the Sioux YMCA. Located in Dupree, South Dakota, this is the only YMCA located on a reservation. Come join other young teen leaders from our YMCA and participate in this once in a lifetime, unique and impactful cultural experience.

Name: Family Story Time
Description: Families and all ages enjoy listening to a story and crafting. Craft materials included.

Name: Youth Leadership Development Club
Description: Youth Leadership Development Club is a weekly leadership club that provides teens the resources to develop their leadership skills in an open and fun environment that inspires learning, discovery, and personal growth.

Name: Starter Spanish
Description: Children receive a basic introduction to Spanish, including greetings, numbers, colors, classroom objects, and more. Children learn songs in Spanish, play games, and color.

Name: Noon Hoops
Description: Join at lunchtime for a drop-in Basketball game for friendly competition in a supportive environment.

Name: Homework Help
Description: Tutors are available for students to drop in and receive help with upcoming assignments, or students may drop in for a study session.

Name: Adult Basketball League
Description: Play as a member on a team and participate in competitive matches.

Name: Youth Basketball Skills
Description: Learn dribbling, passing, catching, shooting and footwork skills, as well as concepts of offense, defense, cooperation, and teamwork.

Name: Floating Beyond Fear
Description: Combines group discussion and pool time in a supportive environment designed to address fear of water.

Name: Youth Basketball League
Description: Practice dribbling, passing, catching, shooting and footwork skills, as well as concepts of offense, defense, cooperation, and teamwork as a member on a team and participate in competitive matches.

Name: Vision Boards
Description: Vision boards are words and images that represent what you want to achieve in the coming months. We will give you the space and supplies you need to define your dreams and create a vision board to remind you to be intentional in working toward your goals.

Name: Youth Flag Football League
Description: Practice foot speed, throwing, and catching, as well as concepts of offense, defense, cooperation, and teamwork as a member on a team and participate in competitive matches.

Name: Youth Baseball League
Description: Practice throwing, catching, hitting and base running skills, as well as concepts of offense, defense, cooperation, and teamwork as a member on a team and participate in competitive matches.

Name: Love and Respect
Description: Research reveals that during marital conflict a husband most often reacts unlovingly when feeling disrespected, and a wife reacts disrespectfully when feeling unloved. Though we all need love and respect equally, the need differs during conflict, and this difference is as different as pink is from blue. Join us for this 10 week course. The cost is per couple and includes a workbook for both.

Name: Youth Baseball Skills
Description: Learn throwing, catching, hitting and base running skills, as well as concepts of offense, defense, cooperation, and teamwork.

Name: Parenting
Description: Receive support and encouragement while learning how to raise responsible children, have more fun in your

Name: Youth Soccer League
Description: Practice dribbling, passing, trapping, shooting, and footwork skills, as well as concepts of offense, defense, cooperation, and teamwork as a member on a team and participate in competitive outdoor matches.

Name: Youth Soccer Skills
Description: Learn dribbling, passing, trapping, shooting, and footwork skills, as well as concepts of offense, defense, cooperation, and teamwork.

Name: Adult Indoor Soccer League
Description: Play and compete in our Adult Indoor Soccer League.  Registration is required.  For members 18 years and older.

Name: Adult Futsol
Description: Similar to indoor soccer, this sport is played between two teams of five players each, one of whom is the goalkeeper. The game is played on a gym using court lines and ball smaller than a traditional soccer ball.

Name: Youth Wrestling Skills
Description: Learn position, motion, changing level, lifting, back step, and back arch position.

Name: Racquetball Reservations
Description: Enjoy a game of racquetball with friendly competition in a supportive environment.

Name: Adult Squash
Description: Enjoy a game of squash with friendly competition in a supportive environment.

Name: Parent/Child Tumbling
Description: This class emphasizes basic motor skills, listening, and following directions in a class setting. Children will work on their hand-eye coordination, body awareness, and improving their strength and flexibility.

Name: Preschool Tumbling
Description: Children work on developing motor skills, body awareness, hand-eye coordination, and improve their strength and flexibility. Activities include an aerobic warm-up and stretching.

Name: Family Gym
Description: Families engage in indoor playtime where children and parents interact with each other. Children develop relationships with peers, work on balance and coordination, and get their wiggles out.

Name: Botukukan Karate
Description: This form of martial arts comes from some of the fluid movements of the conventional Chinese styles, softening the traditional hard style from Okinawa.

Name: ChunJiDo
Description: This progressive art has a strong foundation of traditional values and honor and incorporates Taekwondo and Japanese/Okinawan forms. Learn areas of self-defense in the arts of Kempo, Jujitsu, and Hapkido.

Name: Family Taekwondo
Description: An Olympic style Taekwondo martial art program that teaches the art of kicking, punching, blocking, self-defense, and sparring in a structured environment.

Name: Gymnastics Girls Advanced 2
Description: Proficient achievement of Advanced 1 skills and recommendation from class coach are required to participate in this class. Participants in this class will learn and develop advanced gymnastics skills on all events, and ability to perform all lead up skills correctly is required.

Name: Parent/Child Gymnastics
Description: This class emphasizes basic motor skills, listening, and following directions in a class setting. Children will work on their hand-eye coordination, body awareness, and improving their strength and flexibility. Parent participation is required.

Name: Judo
Description: An introductory class in the Japanese art of self-defense with the short staff. All Japan Kendo Federation Judo is studied to develop basic techniques with the jo (Japanese short staff). All necessary equipment is provided.

Name: Performance Cheerleading
Description: Advanced cheer participants represent their sports teams at all league games and performances.

Name: Sun 73 Tai Chi (1, 2)
Description: Characterized by agile steps with smooth and flowing movements. Sun 73 Tai Chi also emphasizes qigong (exercise to cultivate vital life energy), making it especially effective for healing and relaxation.

Name: Preschool Gymnastics
Description: Classes provide activities that include an aerobic warm-up and stretching. Children will work on developing motor skills, body awareness, hand-eye coordination, and improve their strength and flexibility.

Name: Taekwondo
Description: A Korean art using hands and feet as a means of practical self-defense is recognized as the national sport of Korea as well as an Olympic sport.

Name: Teen Gymnastics
Description: An opportunity for teens to learn new skills and improve coordination, strength, and flexibility. This class is for beginner through advanced gymnasts.

Name: Tai Chi
Description: Tai Chi generates and circulates vital energy around the body by following certain principles of movement, posture and breathing.

Name: Toddler Gym
Description: Toddler Gym is an opportunity for parents to help their young children explore the gymnastics gym under the guidance of trained gymnastics staff. Parent participation is required.

Name: Tang Soo do Karate
Description: Korean martial art emphasizing various blocks, punches, and kicking techniques to promote health, fitness, sport and self-defense.

Name: Beginner Climbing
Description: The first step in learning about climbing and safety techniques, bouldering, climbing terminology, and strength training.

Name: Aikido
Description: This unique system of combat includes punching, striking, and kicking, and focuses on controlling an attacker through locks, throws, and control techniques to guide his or her energy.

Name: Hapkido
Description: This Korean martial arts class teaches self-defense using kicking, throwing, and joint-lock moves. Hapkido means the way of coordinated power and is a ‘soft’ martial art, as it follows the circular and water principles.

Name: Speed Climb
Description: Climbers will learn how to scale the wall the fastest they can using our auto belays. Must pass a beginner class and receive instructor approval before registering.

Name: ChunJiDo
Description: This progressive art has a strong foundation of traditional values and honor and incorporates Taekwondo and Japanese/Okinawan forms. Learn areas of self-defense in the arts of Kempo, Jujitsu, and Hapkido.

Name: Staff-Led Drop-In Climb
Description: Climbing staff will assist with belaying members on the rock wall.

Name: Hapkido
Description: This Korean martial arts class teaches self-defense using kicking, throwing, and joint-lock moves. Hapkido means the way of coordinated power and is a ‘soft’ martial art, as it follows the circular and water principles.

Name: Belay Certification
Description: Learn the safety systems of belaying, knot tying, climbing commands, and proper use of equipment through hands-on climbing instruction.

Name: Judo
Description: An introductory class in the Japanese art of self-defense with the short staff. All Japan Kendo Federation Judo is studied to develop basic techniques with the jo (Japanese short staff). All necessary equipment is provided.

Name: Advanced Climbing
Description: Climbers will practice difficult routes, progressive techniques, and advanced terminology on a competitive level. This is a registered class included in membership. Members must have passed an intermediate class and receive instructor invitation before registering. Climbing shoes are highly recommended at this level.
